## File Structure

```
hotstuff-copy-trading-bot/
├── hotstuff_copy_bot.py   # Main bot
├── requirements.txt       # Python dependencies
├── .env.example           # Config template
├── README.md
└── venv/                  # Python virtual environment (auto-created)
```

---

## Requirements

```
# requirements.txt
requests
msgpack
eth-account
eth-utils
python-dotenv
```

Install:
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

- Python 3.10+
- Hotstuff account with agent wallet
- $120+ USDC in wallet
- Always-on server/VPS for 24/7 operation (Vultr, DigitalOcean, etc.)

---

## VPS Setup (Ubuntu)

```bash
# 1. Update system
apt update && apt upgrade -y

# 2. Install Python
apt install python3 python3-pip python3-venv screen -y

# 3. Clone repo
git clone https://github.com/omgmad/hotstuff-copy-trading-bot
cd hotstuff-copy-trading-bot

# 4. Create venv & install
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 5. Configure
cp .env.example .env
nano .env   # paste your keys

# 6. Run in background
screen -S copybot
python3 hotstuff_copy_bot.py
# Ctrl+A, D to detach
```

